This article contains a '''list of characters''' from the [[Japan]]ese [[anime]] series '''''[[Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann]]'''''.

==Characters==
[[Image:Gurren-Lagann - Simon.jpg<U+200E>|right|150px|thumb|Simon]]
;{{Nihongo|Simon|<U+30B7><U+30E2><U+30F3>|Shimon}}
:{{anime voices|Tetsuya Kakihara}}
:Simon is a fourteen year old digger from Jiiha village. One day, he finds a mysterious drill-shaped item, which is later revealed to be the key for a head-shaped robot he dug up some time earlier. With the help of the robot, Kamina, and Yoko, he fights off a Gunmen who broke into the village. While finishing the Gunmen off with a drill-like attack, they reach the surface world.
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren-Lagann - Kamina.jpg|left|150px|thumb|Kamina]]
;{{Nihongo|Kamina|<U+30AB><U+30DF><U+30CA>}}
:{{anime voices|Katsuyuki Konishi}}
:Kamina is a young man from Jiiha village who dreams of leaving the village and go to the surface, which he saw as a kid. He convinces Simon to help him with his plan to drill through the roof of the village and get to the world above, but the plan failed and he was put in prison. He left the village shortly thereafter with the help of Simon and a young girl named Yoko, as a result of fighting a Gunmen, who broke into the village from the surface.
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren-Lagann - Yoko2.jpg|right|150px|thumb|Yoko]]
;{{Nihongo|Yoko|<U+30E8><U+30FC><U+30B3>|Y<U+014D>ko}}
:{{anime voices|Marina Inoue}}
:Yoko is girl from Jiiha's neighboring village Ritona, who had been chasing the Gunmen which entered Jiiha village. She wields an extensive range of firearms and has previous experience fighting Gunmen. Although she is the same age as Simon, she is mature and one of the most rational of the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dengekionline.com/data/news/2006/7/11/59cc4c329341426fa19bef9660f6ec99.html| title=About Gainax's new series=Dengeki Online|language=Japanese| date=[[February 1]] [[2007]]|accessdate=2007-05-13}}</ref>
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren-Lagann - Leeron.jpg|left|150px|thumb|Leeron]]
;{{Nihongo|Leeron|<U+30EA><U+30FC><U+30ED><U+30F3>|R<U+012B>ron}}
:{{anime voices|Masaya Onosaka}}
:Leeron, or "Lon", is the village mechanic of Ritona who is able to repair and scavenge the various Gunmen he and his group encounter. He is quite knowledgeable, and very flamboyant. Leeron joins Kamina, Simon, and Yoko on their quest to defeat the "Beastmen".
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren-Lagann - Rossiu.jpg|right|150px|thumb|Rossiu]]
;{{Nihongo|Rossiu|<U+30ED><U+30B7><U+30A6>|Roshiu}}
:{{anime voices|Mitsuki Saiga}}
:Rossiu is a boy from another underground village, in which the people worship Gunmen as gods. He looks after Gimmy and Darry, and when they are chosen to leave the village, he decides to go with them, and they join the Gurren Brigade. Before he leaves, the village leader gives him a book that seems to be connected to the Gunmen that guards the village, however, he is illiterate and thus cannot read the book.
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren-Lagann - Gimmy and Darry 2.jpg|left|150px|thumb|Darry (left) and Gimmy]]
;{{Nihongo|Darry|<U+30C0><U+30EA><U+30FC>|Dar<U+012B>}} and {{Nihongo|Gimmy|<U+30AE><U+30DF><U+30FC>|Gim<U+012B>}}
:{{anime voices|Shizuka It<U+014D>}} (Darry), [[Takako Honda]] (Gimmy)
:Darry and Gimmy are children from Rossiu's village, who he cares for. When triplets are born, two people have to be removed from the village and sent to the surface, because the population cannot exceed fifty. Since the two children have no parents, the village leader chooses them to leave the village, however, Rossiu decides to go with them. Gimmy is a typical excitable boy, whilst Darry is a bit shyer, but the two children get along with each other.
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren-Lagann - Viral.jpg|right|150px|thumb|Viral]]
;{{Nihongo|Viral|<U+30F4><U+30A3><U+30E9><U+30EB>|Viraru}}
:{{anime voices|Nobuyuki Hiyama}}
:Viral is a Beastmen who is skilled with Gunmen and close-combat. During a hunting trip, he attacks Kamina, but has to retreat to his Gunmen. He manages to overcome Simon and Kamina's attacks, but leaves before the fight ends since the day has ended. The next day, Kamina and Simon challenge Viral again; this time however, Viral is defeated. Viral barrages Gurren-Lagann with missiles to conceal his escape.
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren Lagann - Zoushi.jpg|left|150px|thumb|Zoushi]]
;Zoushi
:Zoushi appears at the end of episode seven as a new addition to the Gurren Brigade.
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren Lagann - Eyelack.jpg|right|150px|thumb|Eyelack]]
;Eyelack
:Eyelack is a new recruit of the Gurren Brigade that appears in episode seven. His Gunmen has a built in seat on the top, which Yoko uses to fire at enemies.
{{-}} 
[[Image:Gurren Lagann - Kidd.jpg|left|150px|thumb|Kidd]]
;Kidd
:Kidd is another new member of the Gurren Brigade.
{{-}} 
;{{Nihongo|Nia|<U+30CB><U+30A2>}}
:{{anime voices|Yukari Fukui}}
:Nia is a mysterious young girl found sleeping in a capsule in the middle of a river by Simon during the aftermath of episode nine's battle. She doesn't remember who she is or why she was placed in the capsule.

